{
  "texts": [
    "This is done so that it may be evaluated.",
    "The discriminator investigates the relationships between the input, target, and output in order to form an informed opinion on the degree to which the pairs seem to be realistic.",
    "The discriminator's weights are then revised in conformity with both the standard errors of the input/output pair and the input/target pair.",
    "Further alterations to the weights of the generator are informed by the output of the discriminator as well as the variation between the output and the target image.",
    "The generator is composed of two levels, which are as follows: The encoder, which takes the input picture and converts it into a more compact representation of the features, and the decoder, which mimics the appearance of a conventional generator but is really made up of a series of transpose-convolution layers that do the opposite of what the encoder layers do."
  ]
}